    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-03-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-04-13T18:45:32Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Convention Against Torture Implementation Act of 2005 - Directs the Secretary of State to submit to the appropriate congressional committees an annual list of countries where torture is known to be used. </p> <p>Prohibits the direct or indirect transfer or return of persons by the United States or any contractor: (1) to a listed country; or (2) if substantial grounds exist for believing a person would be in danger of torture.</p> <p> Sets forth conditions under which: (1) the Secretary may waive such transfer prohibition; and (2) a treaty-based transfer may occur. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
